WEBVTT

00:03.795 --> 00:07.590
<i>RUDD:</i>
<i>Dr. Orson Rudd, lead scientist,</i>

00:07.674 --> 00:09.926
<i>Ice Shelf Depletion</i>
<i>Investigation</i>

00:10.009 --> 00:12.637
<i>and Antarctic New Species</i>
<i>Project.</i>

00:12.721 --> 00:16.265
<i>NyBy Science Station,</i>
<i>month four of six.</i>

00:16.349 --> 00:19.936
<i>23rd day. 1725 hours.</i>

00:20.019 --> 00:22.063
(wind whistling)

00:24.190 --> 00:27.277
<i>Preliminary results of our</i>
<i>research here is confirming</i>

00:27.360 --> 00:30.029
<i>the thinning of marginal ice</i>

00:30.113 --> 00:32.281
<i>is allowing increases</i>
<i>of sunlight to penetrate</i>

00:32.365 --> 00:34.784
<i>subsurface ocean levels.</i>

00:34.868 --> 00:36.286
<i>This creates an increase</i>

00:36.369 --> 00:38.955
<i>of shallow water sea life</i>
<i>population which causes</i>

00:39.038 --> 00:43.126
<i>migration of deep-sea predators</i>
<i>in search of food.</i>

00:43.209 --> 00:46.254
<i>Most have never</i>
<i>been seen by humans.</i>

00:48.923 --> 00:50.967
<i>Until this crew.</i>

00:59.058 --> 01:00.894
What I'm doing here...

01:06.107 --> 01:09.027
...is gonna save
a million lives.

01:10.069 --> 01:12.906
(music playing over TV)

01:18.161 --> 01:20.163
<i>ROD SERLING (over TV):</i>
<i>The day is April 2nd.</i>

01:20.246 --> 01:22.665
<i>17 miles</i>
<i>off the southwest coast</i>

01:22.749 --> 01:24.334
<i>-of Papua New Guinea...</i>
-(buzzing)

01:24.417 --> 01:26.836
Where the hell is it?

01:26.920 --> 01:28.838
<i>SERLING:</i>
<i>But the launch</i>

01:28.922 --> 01:31.132
<i>of the ship's scientific</i>
<i>submersible</i> Cthulhu

01:31.216 --> 01:33.885
<i>is delayed by the appearance</i>
<i>of a school of 50 squid.</i>

01:33.968 --> 01:37.347
<i>This is the first time the crew</i>
<i>have encountered squid</i>

01:37.430 --> 01:41.309
<i>since departing from the</i>
<i>coastal waters of Australia.</i>

01:41.392 --> 01:44.020
<i>More and more,</i>
<i>the explorers become accustomed</i>

01:44.103 --> 01:47.106
<i>to the unexpected developments</i>
<i>of oceanic life.</i>

01:47.190 --> 01:48.858
(water bubbling)

01:48.942 --> 01:51.027
(speaking in Mandarin)

01:51.110 --> 01:53.196
{\an5}<i>AUTOMATED VOICE:</i>
<i>Have they found</i>
<i>any new species today?</i>

01:53.279 --> 01:54.864
We don't know yet.

01:54.948 --> 01:57.367
Skua and Colvin aren't
back from their dive.

01:57.450 --> 01:59.494
(automated Mandarin
over headphones)

02:04.791 --> 02:06.876
{\an5}<i>SERLING:</i>
<i>Seizing the opportunity</i>
<i>to explore</i>

02:06.960 --> 02:09.878
<i>this swarm of mollusks,</i>
<i>the crew prepare for a dive.</i>

02:09.963 --> 02:12.006
<i>Divers enter the...</i>

02:12.090 --> 02:14.717
Do you know when Kasper
and Doug due back?

02:14.801 --> 02:17.220
<i>...swim amongst a form</i>
<i>of alien life.</i>

02:17.303 --> 02:20.890
<i>The explorers are frail</i>
<i>strangers to this domain.</i>

02:20.974 --> 02:22.892
<i>Soon the presence of the divers</i>

02:22.976 --> 02:25.353
<i>calls the attention</i>
<i>of prowling sharks.</i>

02:25.436 --> 02:27.438
(wind whistling)

02:52.213 --> 02:54.090
(muffled shouting)

02:54.173 --> 02:56.467
ROTIFER:
Kasper!

02:59.053 --> 03:00.972
<i>Unaware of the predators'</i>
<i>dangerous presence,</i>

03:01.055 --> 03:02.932
<i>the unpredictable occurs.</i>

03:03.016 --> 03:06.853
<i>A ten-foot blue shark moves</i>
<i>directly toward the diver.</i>

03:09.147 --> 03:11.900
(muffled screaming)

03:11.983 --> 03:13.151
(both grunting)

03:17.030 --> 03:18.948
<i>...from the environment</i>
<i>which took our ancestors</i>

03:19.032 --> 03:20.366
<i>billions of years to explore...</i>

03:32.921 --> 03:34.088
(yells)

03:34.172 --> 03:35.882
(Skua screaming)

03:40.053 --> 03:42.305
<i>As the divers ascend</i>
<i>through the darkness</i>

03:42.388 --> 03:44.307
<i>to their first</i>
<i>decompression level,</i>

03:44.390 --> 03:47.143
<i>they are intuitively aware</i>
<i>of the murky presence</i>

03:47.226 --> 03:48.436
<i>of death.</i>

03:56.235 --> 03:58.237
(water sloshes)

04:00.198 --> 04:02.200
(soft, wet slapping)

04:07.246 --> 04:09.248
♪ ♪

04:19.425 --> 04:21.427
(creaking)

04:23.596 --> 04:26.516
(thudding)

04:26.599 --> 04:28.977
NARRATOR:
At the bottom of the world,

04:29.060 --> 04:31.187
a group of scientists
is about to encounter

04:31.270 --> 04:34.065
an entity of vast intelligence.

04:34.148 --> 04:37.568
What they are about to learn
will go further and deeper

04:37.652 --> 04:40.863
than anything
they hoped to learn.

04:40.947 --> 04:44.534
Beyond science, beyond fear,

04:44.617 --> 04:48.371
beyond humanity...

04:48.454 --> 04:50.623
in The Twilight Zone.

04:51.416 --> 04:53.209
<i>(The Twilight Zone</i> theme
playing)

04:53.293 --> 04:54.877
<i>NARRATOR: You're traveling</i>
<i>through another dimension,</i>

04:54.961 --> 04:58.381
<i>a dimension not only of</i>
<i>sight and sound but of mind.</i>

04:58.464 --> 05:01.551
<i>It is the middle ground</i>
<i>between light and shadow,</i>

05:01.634 --> 05:04.387
<i>between science</i>
<i>and superstition.</i>

05:04.470 --> 05:07.056
{\an8}<i>And it lies between</i>
<i>the pit of one's fears</i>

05:07.140 --> 05:09.892
{\an8}<i>and the summit</i>
<i>of one's knowledge.</i>

05:09.976 --> 05:13.062
<i>You are now traveling through</i>
<i>a dimension of imagination.</i>

05:13.146 --> 05:17.025
<i>You've just crossed over</i>
<i>into The Twilight Zone.</i>

05:34.000 --> 05:36.002
{\an8}(wind whistling)

05:51.476 --> 05:54.103
{\an8}<i>RUDD (over radio):</i>
<i>Everyone to the diving hut now!</i>

05:54.187 --> 05:57.065
{\an8}(TV playing indistinctly)

06:04.572 --> 06:06.657
{\an8}-FISCH: What the hell happened?
-CARP: Where is Amy?

06:06.741 --> 06:08.284
{\an8}RUDD:
I don't know. S-She's gone.

06:08.367 --> 06:09.952
{\an8}Her suit's over there.

06:10.036 --> 06:11.621
{\an8}Kasper? Douglas?

06:11.704 --> 06:13.331
{\an8}RUDD:
There's no sign of them.

06:13.414 --> 06:15.208
{\an8}Should've both been up
ten minutes ago.

06:18.377 --> 06:20.129
{\an8}Janik, no. You're the only
trained diver we have left.

06:20.213 --> 06:21.964
{\an8}You can't go down there alone.

06:22.048 --> 06:23.299
{\an8}FISCH: Somebody's got to go down
there and find them.

06:23.382 --> 06:24.342
{\an8}RUDD:
And you're high.

06:24.425 --> 06:27.470
{\an8}That thing's tether's
only good for 150 meters.

06:27.553 --> 06:30.348
{\an8}Skua and Colvin were diving to
the ice wall, 450 meters away.

06:30.431 --> 06:31.641
{\an8}RUDD:
You can't go in the water

06:31.724 --> 06:33.142
{\an8}until we know
what happened to them.

06:33.226 --> 06:34.310
{\an8}How will we find out
what happened to them

06:34.393 --> 06:35.436
{\an8}without going in the water?

06:35.520 --> 06:37.396
{\an8}(thudding, sloshing)

07:09.428 --> 07:12.515
{\an8}That octopus.
It's, like, 40 kilos.

07:12.598 --> 07:14.350
{\an8}You don't think...?

07:14.433 --> 07:16.018
{\an8}WEREWOLF LARRY:
You know what?

07:16.102 --> 07:18.479
{\an8}Let's tip over this cooler over
and dump it back in the ocean.

07:18.563 --> 07:19.689
{\an8}(speaking Mandarin)

07:24.235 --> 07:26.028
{\an8}<i>AUTOMATED VOICE:</i>
<i>Don't harm it.</i>

07:26.112 --> 07:28.030
{\an8}<i>-Take it to the lab.</i>
-She's right.

07:28.114 --> 07:29.532
{\an8}Help her take it
back to the lab.

07:29.615 --> 07:31.033
{\an8}Fuck the octopus.

07:31.117 --> 07:32.201
{\an8}It-it could be
the only one of its kind.

07:32.285 --> 07:33.536
{\an8}Who cares?

07:33.619 --> 07:36.247
{\an8}We're wasting time.
Let's go find them.

07:36.330 --> 07:38.499
{\an8}RUDD: Janik, we don't know
what we're dealing with.

07:38.583 --> 07:40.543
{\an8}It's insane to go
back down there alone.

07:40.626 --> 07:43.713
{\an8}Even with double tanks
and seven-millimeter dry gloves,

07:43.796 --> 07:45.548
{\an8}at that depth and temperature,
they got an hour

07:45.631 --> 07:48.384
{\an8}before their hands and feet
become numb and useless.

07:48.467 --> 07:50.094
{\an8}They've been down there
that long already.

07:50.178 --> 07:51.888
{\an8}(device pinging)

07:53.139 --> 07:54.223
{\an8}Visibility's bad.

07:54.307 --> 07:56.642
{\an8}15 meters.

07:57.643 --> 08:00.188
{\an8}(speaking Mandarin)

08:00.271 --> 08:01.731
{\an8}<i>-Help me get this specimen</i>
<i>to the lab.</i>
-Help her take it to the lab.

08:01.814 --> 08:03.357
{\an8}-(grumbles)
-RUDD: Janik.

08:03.441 --> 08:05.860
{\an8}Channing and I will support you
from the surface.

08:26.214 --> 08:28.257
{\an8}(device pinging)

08:57.870 --> 09:00.331
{\an8}<i>RUDD:</i>
<i>Channing, as soon as we can,</i>

09:00.414 --> 09:02.333
{\an8}<i>we need to examine</i>
<i>that octopus.</i>

09:02.416 --> 09:05.127
{\an8}<i>-CARP: I agree.</i>
<i>-It's strange.</i>

09:05.211 --> 09:07.129
Even though Ling
is just an observer

09:07.213 --> 09:08.589
from the Chinese
Antarctic Administration,

09:08.673 --> 09:12.301
did you see how protective
she got of the octopus?

09:12.385 --> 09:15.137
Maybe because she actually cares
about the work?

09:15.221 --> 09:16.639
Hmm.

09:16.722 --> 09:20.226
<i>Maybe.</i>
<i>I think she knows about us.</i>

09:38.953 --> 09:41.956
I hate it down here.
What we're doing.

09:44.250 --> 09:49.839
Channing, you can't say
anything to anyone.

09:49.922 --> 09:53.843
I'm not gonna say
anything to anyone.

09:56.304 --> 09:58.431
What the fuck was that?

09:59.432 --> 10:01.475
RUDD:
What? What is it?

10:07.481 --> 10:09.525
-Jesus.
-(exhales)

10:09.608 --> 10:11.610
(both grunting)

10:15.948 --> 10:17.783
(gasps)

10:22.747 --> 10:25.625
(grunting, straining)

10:32.548 --> 10:34.550
(both panting)

10:46.645 --> 10:49.440
FISCH:
Both shoulders dislocated.

10:49.523 --> 10:51.567
(speaking indistinctly)

10:53.986 --> 10:56.739
Lungs filled with water.

10:56.822 --> 11:00.242
His respirator
was ripped off of him.

11:00.326 --> 11:01.786
He was deep below
sunlight levels.

11:01.869 --> 11:05.581
I only found him
because I saw his headlamp.

11:05.664 --> 11:09.251
And, yeah,
he was caught just, um,

11:09.335 --> 11:12.505
bobbing against
the base of the ice shelf.

11:15.508 --> 11:18.469
I saw no evidence of Doug.
No light, nothing.

11:18.552 --> 11:22.264
(exhales) If Amy fell
in the water without a suit on,

11:22.348 --> 11:23.766
she would have died
within ten minutes.

11:23.849 --> 11:25.893
{\an5}RUDD:
What the hell
could have done that?

11:26.936 --> 11:28.938
(distant whale song, groaning)

11:51.544 --> 11:53.421
Those seals and whales
down there?

11:53.504 --> 11:55.297
They know what happened.

11:55.381 --> 11:56.799
They know that's what
killed them.

11:56.882 --> 11:59.427
WEREWOLF LARRY:
That's right. That's right.

11:59.510 --> 12:01.303
How'd that thing get back
in the cooler

12:01.387 --> 12:02.972
after it killed
Amy, Doug and Kasp?

12:03.055 --> 12:05.307
Do you know how?

12:05.391 --> 12:07.852
'Cause it's that fucking smart.

12:07.935 --> 12:11.355
These things have been around
for millions of years.

12:11.439 --> 12:13.482
(speaking indistinctly)

12:19.738 --> 12:22.825
They don't got bones or a skull.

12:22.908 --> 12:25.327
-There's nothing like them.
-RUDD: Look,

12:25.411 --> 12:28.330
once the satellite's in range,
we can contact McMurdo,

12:28.414 --> 12:30.332
send an emergency response team.

12:30.416 --> 12:33.335
They'll pick up the body,
help us with any search.

12:33.419 --> 12:35.045
TDR satellite will be
at 8.7 degrees.

12:35.129 --> 12:37.339
(speaking Mandarin)

12:37.423 --> 12:40.759
{\an5}<i>AUTOMATED VOICE:</i>
<i>This is not</i>
Megaleledone setebos.

12:42.720 --> 12:44.513
CARP:
Okay. Go ahead.

12:44.597 --> 12:46.599
(Hai speaking indistinctly)

12:48.434 --> 12:50.728
(speaking Mandarin)

12:50.811 --> 12:52.813
<i>AUTOMATED VOICE:</i>
<i>This is another new species.</i>

12:52.897 --> 12:55.900
(Hai speaking Mandarin)

12:55.983 --> 12:58.569
<i>AUTOMATED VOICE:</i>
<i>The radula is not chitinous.</i>

12:58.652 --> 13:01.030
(Hai speaking Mandarin)

13:01.113 --> 13:02.948
<i>It is made</i>
<i>of a harder substance.</i>

13:05.784 --> 13:08.454
<i>This is why we came down here.</i>

13:10.623 --> 13:14.752
<i>To save a species</i>
<i>affected by our behavior.</i>

13:16.795 --> 13:18.672
<i>Living in this water and depth,</i>

13:18.756 --> 13:21.634
<i>it likely has never</i>
<i>encountered a human.</i>

13:22.801 --> 13:24.762
<i>We are the first.</i>

13:24.845 --> 13:25.930
{\an5}FISCH:
I don't care
if it's that thing's

13:26.013 --> 13:27.723
first encounter with anyone.

13:27.806 --> 13:29.850
It'll be his fucking only.

13:31.018 --> 13:33.479
-RUDD: Look out!
-(gasping)

13:37.942 --> 13:39.485
WEREWOLF LARRY:
What the fuck?

13:49.662 --> 13:53.874
Yo. Don't tell me it didn't know
what was going on.

13:53.958 --> 13:55.751
Let's, uh...

13:55.834 --> 13:57.628
(sighs) ...secure Kasper
in the diving hut.

13:57.711 --> 14:00.589
Turn the heater off.

14:00.673 --> 14:02.091
He'll remain preserved
until USAP

14:02.174 --> 14:04.927
can reach us in...
probably three days.

14:05.010 --> 14:06.929
Larry.

14:07.012 --> 14:10.140
Can you fix the lights
and keep an eye on him?

14:12.142 --> 14:14.937
I like animals, okay?

14:15.020 --> 14:18.107
Even the ones I eat,
I'm cool with, yeah?

14:18.190 --> 14:22.611
But I do not want to be in
a room with that motherfucker!

14:22.695 --> 14:25.698
RUDD:
I hear you, Larry. I do.

14:27.199 --> 14:28.784
(speaking Mandarin)

14:28.867 --> 14:31.537
<i>AUTOMATED VOICE:</i>
<i>700 million years ago...</i>

14:34.206 --> 14:37.710
<i>...humans and octopuses were</i>
<i>both an underwater flatworm...</i>

14:42.214 --> 14:45.092
<i>...but evolution</i>
<i>took them their way.</i>

14:46.677 --> 14:49.555
<i>We know that it did.</i>
<i>They don't.</i>

14:52.725 --> 14:55.894
<i>Human minds own this world.</i>

14:55.978 --> 14:59.815
<i>They can feel human...</i>

14:59.898 --> 15:01.984
<i>but they are not.</i>

15:07.823 --> 15:09.700
Just stay away
from its beak and tentacles

15:09.783 --> 15:10.826
and it can't do a thing to you.

15:10.909 --> 15:12.911
Channing? Can you, uh,

15:12.995 --> 15:15.998
print out those USAP emergency
response forms off that e-mail?

15:40.939 --> 15:43.692
{\an5}RUDD (whispering):
Channing, this is the octopus
we've been looking for.

15:43.776 --> 15:46.028
Dr. Hai was right.

15:46.111 --> 15:48.822
The radula is not chitinous.

15:50.783 --> 15:52.868
The chromatophores
are reflective.

15:52.951 --> 15:54.662
This is the new species

15:54.745 --> 15:55.871
<i>(over phone):</i>
<i>Troxell sent us here to find.</i>

15:55.954 --> 15:58.040
<i>The chemicals we can extract</i>
<i>from it will revolutionize</i>

15:58.123 --> 16:01.710
<i>pain management, anesthesia,</i>
<i>you name it.</i>

16:03.045 --> 16:04.046
<i>Once the satellite is up,</i>

16:04.129 --> 16:05.547
<i>let's send a message</i>

16:05.631 --> 16:07.675
<i>that we have secured</i>
<i>the specimen.</i>

16:12.638 --> 16:15.140
(speaking indistinctly)

16:42.126 --> 16:44.128
(keyboard clicking)

16:53.679 --> 16:55.347
(keyboard clicking)

17:18.037 --> 17:20.622
{\an5}<i>CARP (over phone):</i>
<i>Orson, I did not sign up</i>
<i>for this.</i>

17:20.705 --> 17:23.166
{\an5}<i>RUDD:</i>
<i>You're not thinking</i>
<i>about the big picture.</i>

17:23.250 --> 17:24.960
Let's just put
this goddamn thing

17:25.042 --> 17:26.627
back in the water and walk away.

17:26.712 --> 17:29.006
No.

17:44.730 --> 17:48.067
(upbeat music playing)

18:00.871 --> 18:02.873
(thudding)

18:14.384 --> 18:16.386
(muffled music playing)

18:22.851 --> 18:25.062
{\an8}What if we just let Janik
or Larry kill it?

18:25.145 --> 18:28.315
{\an8}You know, we could say,
"What could we do?"

18:28.398 --> 18:30.192
<i>(automated voice</i>
<i>speaking Mandarin)</i>

18:32.402 --> 18:34.404
(whales singing, groaning)

18:40.494 --> 18:43.372
(upbeat music continues playing)

19:00.472 --> 19:02.516
♪ ♪

19:12.818 --> 19:14.820
♪ ♪

19:37.509 --> 19:39.511
♪ ♪

20:05.329 --> 20:07.331
♪ ♪

20:22.387 --> 20:24.556
(whales singing, groaning)

20:34.900 --> 20:36.902
Satellite's up
in a few minutes.

20:41.198 --> 20:43.325
It's time to go to work.

20:46.036 --> 20:48.038
(upbeat music playing)

20:50.624 --> 20:52.542
Hey, Larry, you don't see this?

20:52.626 --> 20:54.670
The pipe's busted.

20:57.255 --> 20:58.507
Larry.

20:58.590 --> 21:00.467
♪ ♪

21:14.940 --> 21:16.274
(Fisch gasping)

21:22.406 --> 21:24.700
(groaning)

21:30.956 --> 21:32.958
(straining)

21:43.135 --> 21:45.178
♪ ♪

22:02.154 --> 22:05.073
{\an5}<i>RUDD (over phone):</i>
<i>As soon as the satellite's</i>
<i>over the horizon</i>

22:05.157 --> 22:07.242
and the Internet's live,
I'll contact McMurdo Station

22:07.325 --> 22:09.327
to send a rescue party.

22:09.411 --> 22:10.704
Then you alert Troxell.

22:20.172 --> 22:22.174
(beeps, chimes)

22:23.508 --> 22:26.178
Shit.

22:26.261 --> 22:29.097
I need that two-step
verification code,

22:29.181 --> 22:31.433
and the app is on my phone.

22:31.516 --> 22:33.101
<i>CARP:</i>
<i>Have you seen my phone?</i>

22:33.185 --> 22:34.603
<i>RUDD:</i>
<i>You had it in the lab.</i>

22:42.110 --> 22:43.779
(exhales)

22:55.207 --> 22:57.667
Hey, have you seen my phone?

22:57.751 --> 23:00.504
<i>CARP:</i>
<i>Larry?</i>

23:03.507 --> 23:04.966
(gasps)

23:05.050 --> 23:05.967
(squishes)

23:06.051 --> 23:07.803
(panting)

23:14.059 --> 23:15.977
<i>RUDD:</i>
<i>Channing, w-what's wrong?</i>

23:16.061 --> 23:18.230
<i>CARP:</i>
<i>Janik. Larry...</i>

23:29.741 --> 23:32.160
-Shit.
-(speaking Mandarin)

23:32.244 --> 23:34.830
<i>AUTOMATED VOICE:</i>
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

23:42.087 --> 23:43.672
♪ ♪

24:01.815 --> 24:03.859
(nearby clattering)

24:09.114 --> 24:11.533
RUDD:
They're all gone.

24:11.616 --> 24:13.034
Do you see anything?

24:13.118 --> 24:14.536
In the tanks or on the floor?

24:14.619 --> 24:15.704
CARP:
If we see one?

24:15.787 --> 24:17.664
We kill it.

24:17.747 --> 24:19.749
No!
(speaking Mandarin)

24:19.833 --> 24:21.668
Five are dead.
Why wouldn't we kill it?

24:21.751 --> 24:24.212
I heard my phone in her room.

24:24.296 --> 24:26.464
She overheard everything
we were saying.

24:26.548 --> 24:30.177
She knows we're not really here
studying the ice.

24:30.260 --> 24:32.095
(speaking Mandarin)

24:32.179 --> 24:34.097
<i>AUTOMATED VOICE:</i>
<i>We knew of Troxell's interest</i>

24:34.181 --> 24:35.849
<i>in this species of octopus</i>

24:35.932 --> 24:38.727
<i>three months before</i>
<i>you even arrived here.</i>

24:38.810 --> 24:40.061
(gasps)

24:40.145 --> 24:42.022
It has my phone.

24:44.608 --> 24:47.861
(creaking)

24:53.867 --> 24:58.246
Orson, the projector, the laptop

24:58.330 --> 25:00.248
are both controlled by my phone.

25:00.332 --> 25:02.417
It's tapping into
Ling's computer.

25:02.500 --> 25:05.420
-RUDD: The octopus?
-It figured it out.

25:05.503 --> 25:08.548
-It's broken into her research.
-RUDD: What is this?

25:08.632 --> 25:11.384
What do you need
all this data for?

25:14.304 --> 25:17.933
An animal,
three hours out of the ocean,

25:18.016 --> 25:20.519
is running
my fucking cell phone?

25:20.602 --> 25:22.520
Tell us what you know.

25:22.604 --> 25:24.898
Chinese military?

25:27.192 --> 25:29.778
So, it also wants to know.

25:29.861 --> 25:32.239
What you're really doing here
is, let's see...

25:35.367 --> 25:37.118
You're investigating
the physical mechanisms

25:37.202 --> 25:39.079
of this octopus?

25:39.162 --> 25:42.499
Artificial skin? Soft robots?

25:42.582 --> 25:44.542
Invisibility cloaking?

25:44.626 --> 25:46.294
(speaking Mandarin)

25:46.378 --> 25:48.171
<i>AUTOMATED VOICE:</i>
<i>You always think so small.</i>

25:49.589 --> 25:51.132
<i>We will use this animal</i>

25:51.216 --> 25:53.385
<i>to change</i>
<i>what a human being can be.</i>

25:56.012 --> 25:58.807
<i>What we're after</i>
<i>is no different than you.</i>

25:58.890 --> 26:01.935
We're trying to develop it
to save lives, not take them.

26:03.353 --> 26:05.021
<i>AUTOMATED VOICE:</i>
<i>This octopus is unique.</i>

26:05.105 --> 26:07.941
<i>We've both been</i>
<i>searching for it.</i>

26:09.567 --> 26:12.112
You want to exploit
the neurological properties

26:12.195 --> 26:14.197
of this octopus species?

26:15.907 --> 26:18.493
-Gene edit into a human egg...
-(gasps)

26:18.576 --> 26:20.036
...giving human beings
the best traits

26:20.120 --> 26:21.621
of vertebrates and cephalopods.

26:21.705 --> 26:25.625
So, if you bioengineer
this gene...

26:27.252 --> 26:31.006
...you would create
a new species of human.

26:31.089 --> 26:33.508
Our arms and skin would have
the ability to taste,

26:33.591 --> 26:37.012
see and react without reporting
to a centralized brain.

26:37.095 --> 26:39.306
To camouflage
to its surroundings.

26:39.389 --> 26:42.309
We'd be able to live
in the oceans

26:42.392 --> 26:44.394
while controlling the land.

26:45.437 --> 26:46.855
(metal creaking)

26:46.938 --> 26:48.523
Let's be honest with ourselves.

26:48.606 --> 26:51.568
We're both trying to take from
this animal what we don't have.

26:53.320 --> 26:54.529
That's what human beings do.

26:55.613 --> 26:58.199
It's what we've always done.

26:58.283 --> 26:59.951
I was wrong.

27:00.035 --> 27:04.164
We put it back in the sea,
and we go home.

27:07.417 --> 27:09.002
(gasps)

27:13.631 --> 27:16.301
(muffled groaning)

27:24.517 --> 27:26.019
RUDD:
Come on.

27:31.608 --> 27:33.068
(panting)

27:33.151 --> 27:35.528
{\an8}-RUDD: You okay?
-Yeah.

27:45.246 --> 27:47.123
(creaking)

28:08.353 --> 28:10.980
(panting)

28:11.064 --> 28:13.441
{\an8}CARP:
What the hell is happening?

28:13.525 --> 28:17.404
{\an8}RUDD: Oh, my God.
It changed the sequence.

28:24.702 --> 28:27.747
It figured out that if somehow,

28:27.831 --> 28:30.125
during this operation,
there were to occur

28:30.208 --> 28:33.711
a mutation or sabotage
of genetic material,

28:33.795 --> 28:37.424
and this same gene
is manipulated for octopus DNA,

28:37.507 --> 28:40.135
the opposite would occur.

28:40.218 --> 28:45.140
Sea life could rise out of the
ocean and stop life on land.

28:45.223 --> 28:49.144
It would do what evolution
didn't 700 million years ago:

28:49.227 --> 28:51.771
put an end to the human species.

28:53.565 --> 28:55.567
♪ ♪

29:14.419 --> 29:16.463
♪ ♪

29:28.475 --> 29:32.729
{\an5}NARRATOR:
What if our role has always been
not to rule this world,

29:32.812 --> 29:34.647
but to prime it?

29:34.731 --> 29:39.569
To lay the foundation for the
true inheritors of the Earth?

29:39.652 --> 29:44.199
The reign of humankind
has come to a close today,

29:44.282 --> 29:48.203
here in the dark, icy waters

29:48.286 --> 29:50.330
of The Twilight Zone.

